article.headline: Tennessee Tech 117, Bluefield College 85
article.story: COOKEVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Derek Stribling scored 22 points, Antjuan Koger added 21 and six Golden Eagles scored in double figures as Tennessee Tech beat Bluefield 117-85 Tuesday night. Stribling went 10 for 10 from the field for the Golden Eagles (2-1), and also had six rebounds, five assists and four steals. Koger's 21 points included 10 for 11 from the line. Bluefield (4-3) had four players in double figures, led by Ben Smalls with 20 points. Anthony Hodges added 13, and Cedric Brown and Curtis Dixon each scored 11. The Rams briefly led 8-5 in the first, before the Golden Eagles had a 12-4 run in the first half to open a 15-point lead and later ended the half ahead 59-36. The Rams cut it to under 20 points in the second half on a layup and dunk by Smalls to start the second half, making it 59-40, but the Golden Eagles responded with a 12-2 run, once stretching the lead to 38 points.
